Annotation.note:
Compute the distance of the point $M=(ma,mb,mc)$ from a super
ellipsoid with half axes $a,b,c$ with the Lagrange multiplier method.

In the general equations $k$ is the super ellipsoid's exponent and
$(x,y,z)$ the point on the super ellipsoid closest to $M$.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Maple
polys:=[(x/a)^k + (y/b)^k + (z/c)^k - 1,
	a^k*(x-ma) + k*x^(k-1)*l,
	b^k*(y-mb) + k*y^(k-1)*l,
	c^k*(z-mc) + k*z^(k-1)*l];
vars:=[l,x,y,z];
parameters:=[ma,mb,mc,a,b,c];
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
Geometry
\end{keywords}

First discussed in [BIB/Buchberger_87a]
